# Project Overview and Product Development Requirements (PDR)

## 1. Project Information
- **Project Name**: aimateflutter (AiMate App)
- **Description**: A Flutter mobile application designed for AI bot exploration, interaction, character creation, and user management. It provides a platform for users to chat with AI bots, create their own AI characters, and manage their profiles.
- **Version**: 1.0.0+1
- **Target Platforms**: Mobile (iOS, Android - inferred from Flutter project type)

## 2. Core Features and User Stories

### 2.1. User Onboarding & Authentication
- **User Story**: As a new user, I want to be able to easily sign up and log in to the app so I can access its features.
- **Features**:
    - Onboarding flow (onboarding_screen.dart, start_screen.dart)
    - User registration
    - User login
    - Session management

### 2.2. AI Bot Exploration & Interaction
- **User Story**: As a user, I want to discover and explore various AI bots, and interact with them through chat, so I can find companions or tools that suit my needs.
- **Features**:
    - Bot exploration (explore_screen.dart)
    - Bot details and information (character_information_screen.dart)
    - Chat interface for bot interaction (chat_screen.dart, conversation_screen.dart)
    - AI bot listing and categorization

### 2.3. Character Creation & Customization
- **User Story**: As a creative user, I want to be able to create and customize my own AI characters so I can bring my unique ideas to life.
- **Features**:
    - AI character creation interface (create_my_character_screen.dart)
    - Customization options for AI characters
    - Management of created bots (my_bot_screen.dart)

### 2.4. User Profile Management
- **User Story**: As a user, I want to manage my personal profile and settings so I can personalize my app experience.
- **Features**:
    - User profile viewing and editing (profile_screen.dart)
    - Account settings

### 2.5. In-App Purchases
- **User Story**: As a user, I want to be able to make in-app purchases so I can unlock premium features or content.
- **Features**:
    - Purchase flow and management (purchase_screen.dart)
    - Integration with payment gateways (inferred)

### 2.6. Notifications
- **User Story**: As a user, I want to receive important notifications so I can stay updated on app activities or messages.
- **Features**:
    - Notification display (notification_screen.dart)

### 2.7. General App Functionality
- **User Story**: As a user, I want a smooth and responsive application experience with clear navigation.
- **Features**:
    - Centralized navigation
    - Loading indicators (loading_screen.dart)
    - Image viewing (detail_image_screen.dart)
    - Theming and consistent UI/UX

## 3. Technical Requirements

### 3.1. Performance
- **Responsiveness**: Application should be highly responsive with smooth animations and transitions.
- **Load Times**: Fast loading times for screens and data fetching.
- **Efficiency**: Optimized resource usage for battery and memory.

### 3.2. Scalability
- **API Handling**: Robust API client capable of handling increased load and various response types.
- **Data Storage**: Scalable local storage for user preferences and cached data.

### 3.3. Security
- **API Security**: Secure communication with backend APIs (e.g., HTTPS).
- **Data Protection**: Protection of sensitive user data, both in transit and at rest.
- **Authentication**: Secure user authentication and authorization mechanisms.

### 3.4. Maintainability
- **Code Quality**: Adherence to Dart/Flutter best practices and coding standards.
- **Modularity**: Modular architecture to facilitate easy feature development and maintenance.
- **Testability**: Code designed for easy unit and widget testing.

### 3.5. User Experience
- **Intuitive UI**: Clean, intuitive, and consistent user interface.
- **Accessibility**: Consideration for accessibility standards.
- **Theming**: Support for consistent application theming.

### 3.6. Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Flutter
- **Language**: Dart
- **State Management**: Provider with ChangeNotifierProvider
- **Networking**: Dio for HTTP requests
- **Local Storage**: shared_preferences

### 3.7. Error Handling
- Comprehensive error handling for API calls, local storage, and UI interactions.
- User-friendly error messages.
